opical troposphere (2000) Science, 287, pp. 1242-1245; Halberstam, I., Schieldge, J.P., Anomalous behaviour of the atmospheric surface layer over a melting snowpack (1981) J. Appl. Meteorol., 20, pp. 255-265; Hastenrath, S., Heat-budget on the Quelccaya ice cap, Peruvian Andes (1978) J. Glaciol., 20 (82), pp. 85-97; Hastenrath, S., (1981) The Glaciation of the Ecuadorian Andes, p. 173. , A. A. Balkema, Brookfield, Vt; Hastenrath, S., (1991) Climate Dynamics of the Tropics, p. 488. , Kluwer Acad., Norwell, Mass; Hastenrath, S., Kruss, P.D., The dramatic retreat of Mount Kenya's glaciers between 1963 and 1987: Greenhouse forcing (1992) Ann. Glaciol., 16, pp. 127-133; Hock, R., Modelling of glacier melt and discharge (1998), p. 126. , Ph.D. thesis, ETH Geograph. Inst., ETH Zürich, Zurich, SwitzerlandHock, R., Holmgren, B., Some aspects of energy balance and ablation of Storglaciären, northern Sweden (1996) Geograf. Ann. A, 78, pp. 121-131; Kaser, G., Glacier-climate interaction at low-latitudes (2001) J. Glaciol., 47 (157), pp. 195-204; Kaser, G., Osmaston, H.A., (2002) Tropical Glaciers, p. 228. , Cambridge Univ. Press, New York; Kaser, G., Ames, M., Zamora, M., Glacier fluctuation and climate in the Cordillera Blanca, Peru (1990) Ann. Glaciol., 14, pp. 136-141; King, J.C., Anderson, P.S., Heat and water vapour fluxes and scalar roughness lengths over an Antartic Ice Shelf (1994) Boundary Layer Meteorol., 69, pp. 101-121; Klok, E.J., Oerlemans, J., Model study of the spatial distribution of the energy and mass balance of Morteratschgleischer, Switzerland (2002) J. Glaciol., 48 (163), pp. 505-518; Kuhn, M., Climate and glaciers (1981) Sea Level, Ice and Climatic Change (Proceedings of the Canberra Symposium), 131, pp. 3-20. , IAHS Publ; Male, D.H., Granger, R.J., Snow surface energy exchange (1981) Water Resour Res., 17 (3), pp. 609-627; Marks, D., Dozier, J., Climate and energy exchange at the snow surface in the alpine region of the Sierra Nevada: 2. Snow cover energ